cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use or build on this work — in particular the two-phase "polite
  shrink" storage-arc controller — please cite it as below. Published openly;
  no exclusivity is claimed. This record exists to date and attribute the
  ideas.
type: software
title: >-
  Dynamic DHT Storage-Arc Sizing: Controller Design, Robustness Evidence, and
  a Reference Implementation for Kitsune2 (two-phase "polite shrink")
authors:
  - family-names: John
    given-names: Ceri
    alias: topeuph-ai
date-released: "2026-07-12"
repository-code: "https://github.com/ValiChord/ValiChord"
url: "https://github.com/ValiChord/ValiChord/tree/research/dht-arc-sharding-sim/research/arc_sim"
abstract: >-
  A dynamic storage-arc controller for kitsune2 (Holochain's DHT layer),
  addressing the control-loop oscillation that led to arcs being fixed at
  FULL in 2021 (kitsune2 issue #160). Core mechanism: a two-phase "polite
  shrink" — announce an intent to vacate, wait a multiple of measured gossip
  staleness, re-check counting lower-agent-id intenders as already gone, with
  deterministic asymmetric conflict resolution motivated by TCAS coordinated
  complementary resolution advisories (suggested by C. John). Evidence:
  4,992 paired simulations (0 sector losses in 1,248 runs for the winning
  variant), an evolutionary adversarial search, a kitsune2 reference
  implementation with an 8-node storm test, and Wind Tunnel measurements
  over real iroh transport surviving a 33% simultaneous node loss with no
  sector ever orphaned. Research programme conceived and directed by Ceri
  John; design elaboration, implementation, and analysis executed with AI
  assistance (Claude, Anthropic); all results human-reviewed.
keywords:
  - distributed-hash-table
  - dht-sharding
  - storage-arcs
  - holochain
  - kitsune2
  - control-loop
  - polite-shrink
